# Class: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200046> (fossa for lacrimal sac of lacrimal bone)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200046> "A bone fossa situated on the anterior part of the medial orbital wall, formed by the frontal process of the maxilla and the lacrimal bone; it lodges the lacrimal sac and communicates inferiorly with the nasolacrimal canal, which drains tears into the inferior nasal meatus.")
