# Class: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200087> (inferior articular facet of fifth thoracic vertebra)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200087> "A zone of bone organ located on the inferior articular process of the fifth thoracic vertebra, facing anteroinferiorly and oriented in the coronal plane. It articulates with the superior articular facet of T6, forming the zygapophyseal joint at the upper-mid thoracic junction that limits flexion-extension and permits limited rotation.")
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.org/dc/terms/date> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200087> "2026-03-19T00:00:00Z"^^xsd:dateTime)
