# Class: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200094> (inferior articular facet of second thoracic vertebra)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200094> "A zone of bone organ located on the inferior articular process of the second thoracic vertebra, facing anteroinferiorly and oriented in the coronal plane. It articulates with the superior articular facet of T3, forming the zygapophyseal joint that limits flexion and facilitates the slight rotatory mobility characteristic of the mid-thoracic region.")
