# Class: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200099> (inferior articular facet of tenth thoracic vertebra)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200099> "A zone of bone organ located on the inferior articular process of the tenth thoracic vertebra, facing anteroinferiorly. It articulates with the superior articular facet of T11 at the zygapophyseal joint; T10 is a transitional vertebra and its inferior facets may begin to adopt a more sagittally oriented profile approaching the lumbar pattern.")
