# Class: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200102> (inferior articular facet of twelfth thoracic vertebra)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200102> "A zone of bone organ located on the inferior articular process of the twelfth thoracic vertebra. T12 is the most transitional thoracic vertebra; its inferior articular facets face laterally, closely resembling the lumbar pattern, and articulate with the superior articular facets of L1 at the thoracolumbar junction.")
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.org/dc/terms/date> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200102> "2026-03-19T00:00:00Z"^^xsd:dateTime)
