# Class: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200130> (mammillary process of first lumbar vertebra)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200130> "A process of vertebra located on the posterior surface of the superior articular process of the first lumbar vertebra, presenting as a small bony tubercle. It serves as an attachment site for the multifidus muscle and marks the most superior of the lumbar mammillary processes, situated just below the thoracolumbar junction.")
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.org/dc/terms/date> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200130> "2026-03-19T00:00:00Z"^^xsd:dateTime)
