# Class: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200166> (pecten pubis of pubis of os coxa)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200166> "A zone of bone organ forming the sharp, ridge-like superior border of the superior pubic ramus of the pubis of the os coxa (innominate bone), extending from the pubic tubercle to the iliopectineal eminence and forming part of the pelvic brim, with the pectineus muscle attaching to its anterior surface.")
