# Class: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200173> (posterior clinoid process of sphenoid bone)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200173> "A skeletal element projection situated at each superolateral angle of the dorsum sellae of the sphenoid bone, projecting anterolaterally; it provides attachment for the tentorium cerebelli and the petrosphenoidal ligament, and serves as a landmark for the abducens nerve as it bends over the petrous apex.")
