# Class: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200179> (pterygoid fossa of sphenoid bone)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200179> "A bone fossa formed by the concave medial surface of the lateral pterygoid plate facing the pterygoid process, situated between the lateral and medial pterygoid plates of the sphenoid bone; it provides origin for the medial pterygoid muscle and the lower belly of the lateral pterygoid muscle.")
