# Class: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200192> (sacral hiatus of sacrum)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200192> "A bone foramen forming the inferior opening of the sacral canal, resulting from the failure of fusion of the laminae of S4 and S5, and bounded laterally by the sacral cornua; it provides clinical access to the epidural space for caudal anaesthetic injections.")
