# Class: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200206> (spinous process of first cervical vertebra)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200206> "A neural spine reduced to a small posterior tubercle on the posterior arch of the atlas (C1), representing a vestigial spinous process that lacks the bifid tip seen in typical cervical vertebrae and serves as attachment for the ligamentum nuchae and the rectus capitis posterior minor muscle.")
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.org/dc/terms/date> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200206> "2026-03-19T00:00:00Z"^^xsd:dateTime)
