# Class: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200218> (sternal end of tenth rib)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200218> "A zone of bone organ forming the anterior extremity of the tenth rib, which ends in a small cap of cartilage that fuses with the costal arch rather than attaching independently to the sternum. The tenth rib is a false rib and, together with ribs eight and nine, contributes to the inferior costal margin.")
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.org/dc/terms/date> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200218> "2026-03-19T00:00:00Z"^^xsd:dateTime)
