# Class: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200232> (superior articular facet of first lumbar vertebra)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200232> "A zone of bone organ forming the articular surface on the superior articular process of the first lumbar vertebra, oriented in the sagittal plane with a concave, medially facing articular surface. It articulates with the inferior articular facet of the twelfth thoracic vertebra, forming the uppermost zygapophyseal joint of the lumbar column.")
