# Class: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200240> (superior articular facet of second thoracic vertebra)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200240> "A zone of bone organ located on the superior articular process of the second thoracic vertebra, facing posteriorly and oriented predominantly in the coronal plane. It articulates with the inferior articular facet of T1 at the zygapophyseal joint, guiding movement and limiting axial rotation in the upper thoracic spine.")
