# Class: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200254> (superior nuchal line of squamous part of occipital bone)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200254> "A zone of bone organ forming the upper of two curved ridges on the external surface of the squamous occipital bone, extending laterally from the external occipital protuberance. It provides attachment for the trapezius, sternocleidomastoid, and splenius capitis muscles.")
