# Class: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200286> (tympanic caniliculus of petrous part of temporal bone)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200286> "A zone of bone organ forming a small canal in the floor of the jugular fossa of the petrous part of the temporal bone, transmitting the tympanic nerve (Jacobson's nerve), a branch of the glossopharyngeal nerve (CN IX), to the tympanic cavity where it contributes to the tympanic plexus.")
