# Class: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200305> (vertebral arch of sixth thoracic vertebra)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200305> "A neural arch forming the posterior bony ring of the sixth thoracic vertebra, comprising paired pedicles and broad laminae enclosing the vertebral foramen. Located near the thoracic kyphotic apex, it bears a long, inferiorly inclined spinous process and transverse processes with costal facets that articulate with the tubercle of the sixth rib.")
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.org/dc/terms/date> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_1200305> "2026-03-19T00:00:00Z"^^xsd:dateTime)
